    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot (with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>in 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[675ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[900ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
