            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>halved lemongrass</strong>, <strong>rinsed lentils </strong>and <strong>drained chickpeas </strong>to the pot and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>coconut stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 15-20 min, stirring occasionally, until all the water is absorbed and the lentils are tender – this is your <strong>lentil & chickpea dal</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
